1
00:01:48,024 --> 00:01:50,049
My dear children...

2
00:01:50,160 --> 00:01:53,357
it is now better
than several years...

3
00:01:53,463 --> 00:01:55,624
since I moved to New York...

4
00:01:55,732 --> 00:01:58,428
and I haven't seen you
as much as I would like to.

5
00:02:00,036 --> 00:02:04,063
I hope you will come
to this ceremony of papal honors...

6
00:02:04,174 --> 00:02:06,062
given for my charitable work.

7
00:02:08,545 --> 00:02:11,969
The only wealth
in this world is children.

8
00:02:12,082 --> 00:02:16,041
More than all the money,
power on earth...

9
00:02:16,152 --> 00:02:18,040
you are my treasure.

10
00:02:20,256 --> 00:02:22,588
Anthony and Mary...

11
00:02:22,692 --> 00:02:25,024
although I entrusted
your education to your mother...

12
00:02:25,128 --> 00:02:27,494
for your own best interests...

13
00:02:27,597 --> 00:02:30,088
you know how I look forward
to seeing you...

14
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:33,260
and to a new period
of harmony in our lives.

15
00:02:34,704 --> 00:02:37,264
Perhaps you might
prevail upon your mother...

16
00:02:37,374 --> 00:02:39,672
to come to this celebration...

17
00:02:39,776 --> 00:02:42,301
and that from time to time...

18
00:02:42,412 --> 00:02:46,200
we can all see each other
at family functions.

19
00:02:46,316 --> 00:02:50,980
Anyway, I remain,
your loving father.

20
00:03:20,650 --> 00:03:22,880
Hail Mary, full of grace...

21
00:03:26,756 --> 00:03:28,747
blessed art Thou amongst women...

22
00:03:30,126 --> 00:03:34,222
and blessed is the fruit
of Thy womb,Jesus.

23
00:03:34,330 --> 00:03:37,163
Holy Mary, mother of God...

24
00:03:37,267 --> 00:03:39,633
pray for us sinners--

25
00:04:03,226 --> 00:04:06,582
Almighty God,
bless the insignia...

26
00:04:06,696 --> 00:04:09,256
of Saint Sebastian the Martyr...

27
00:04:09,365 --> 00:04:13,654
that it may contribute
to the sacredness of him...

28
00:04:13,770 --> 00:04:15,692
to whom it is given.

29
00:04:28,118 --> 00:04:30,006
Do you, Michael...

30
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:33,248
promise to be faithful
to the noble purposes...

31
00:04:33,356 --> 00:04:35,278
of this order...

32
00:04:35,391 --> 00:04:38,519
to have a special care
for the poor, the needy...

33
00:04:38,628 --> 00:04:40,391
and those who are ill?

34
00:04:40,497 --> 00:04:42,294
l do so promise.

35
00:04:57,280 --> 00:05:00,636
May the blessing
of Almighty God--

36
00:05:00,750 --> 00:05:05,710
Father, Son, and Holy Spirit--

37
00:05:05,822 --> 00:05:09,986
descend upon you
and remain with you...

38
00:05:10,093 --> 00:05:11,458
forever.

39
00:05:11,561 --> 00:05:13,188
Amen.

40
00:06:45,021 --> 00:06:46,579
Vincent, our name's
not on the list.

41
00:06:50,126 --> 00:06:51,423
Write it in.

42
00:06:51,527 --> 00:06:54,018
Mancini. M-A-N-C-l-N-l.

43
00:06:55,798 --> 00:06:58,426
- ls there a problem?
- My name's not on the list.

44
00:06:58,534 --> 00:07:00,957
Then you have to
leave immediately.

45
00:07:01,070 --> 00:07:03,368
- No two ways about it.
- You want to dance?

46
00:07:03,473 --> 00:07:06,169
Joe, it's Vinnie.
lt's okay. These are our guests.

47
00:07:07,010 --> 00:07:08,409
l'm sorry, Dave.

48
00:07:08,511 --> 00:07:11,400
lt's all right.
Vinnie, welcome to the party.

49
00:08:04,334 --> 00:08:05,733
Good to see you.

50
00:08:05,835 --> 00:08:08,690
lt's good to see you again.
This is my husband.

51
00:08:08,805 --> 00:08:10,693
This is my son, Anthony.

52
00:08:11,808 --> 00:08:14,697
The order of Saint Sebastian
is one of the highest honors...

53
00:08:14,811 --> 00:08:16,836
the Catholic Church
can bestow upon a layman.

54
00:08:16,946 --> 00:08:19,744
The award was first granted
by Pope Gregory--

55
00:08:19,849 --> 00:08:22,773
What about Mr. Corleone's connections
with Las Vegas gambling?

56
00:08:22,885 --> 00:08:25,217
Press kits have pictures--

57
00:08:25,321 --> 00:08:27,482
How about his involvement
with the underworld?

58
00:08:27,590 --> 00:08:29,080
Cut the crap, huh?

59
00:08:29,158 --> 00:08:32,423
The pope,
the Holy Father himself...

60
00:08:32,528 --> 00:08:35,224
has this very day
blessed Michael Corleone.

61
00:08:35,331 --> 00:08:37,219
You think you know
better than the pope?

62
00:08:37,333 --> 00:08:39,221
- Do it, do it.
- Vincent!

63
00:08:39,335 --> 00:08:41,724
- Yes?
- She loves you.

64
00:08:46,843 --> 00:08:48,333
- What'd he say?
- l love you too.

65
00:08:54,450 --> 00:08:57,977
Hi, Vincent.
l remember you.

66
00:08:59,155 --> 00:09:00,679
You remember me?
From where?

67
00:09:00,790 --> 00:09:03,179
When we were at
a party together.

68
00:09:03,292 --> 00:09:05,180
Did you come to the club?

69
00:09:05,294 --> 00:09:07,785
- No, it was a wedding.
- A wedding?

70
00:09:08,898 --> 00:09:12,390
l was eight, and you were 1 5.

71
00:09:12,502 --> 00:09:15,528
l had a lot of girlfriends
when l was 1 5.

72
00:09:15,638 --> 00:09:17,833
- Eight-year-olds?
- Especially eight-year-olds.

73
00:09:19,976 --> 00:09:22,103
Where's Mary?

74
00:09:22,211 --> 00:09:24,600
Would somebody please hail Mary?

75
00:09:24,714 --> 00:09:26,909
Excuse me, Your Excellency.

76
00:09:27,016 --> 00:09:29,940
You know, you haven't
kissed me hello yet.

77
00:09:30,052 --> 00:09:33,180
- Relatives always kiss.
- Oh, now we're related?

78
00:09:33,289 --> 00:09:35,814
l'm your little cousin.

79
00:09:42,832 --> 00:09:44,561
Who's your father?

80
00:09:44,667 --> 00:09:47,363
l'll give you a hint.

81
00:09:47,470 --> 00:09:49,995
- He's ltalian.
- Mary.

82
00:09:50,106 --> 00:09:52,961
Mary, we've been
waiting for you.

83
00:09:53,075 --> 00:09:55,168
Remember...

84
00:09:55,278 --> 00:09:57,075
keep your voice low.

85
00:09:57,180 --> 00:09:59,705
Smile. Don't forget to smile.

86
00:10:17,433 --> 00:10:19,264
Carissimi Amici...

87
00:10:19,368 --> 00:10:21,256
the honorary chairman...

88
00:10:21,370 --> 00:10:23,634
of the Vito Corleone
Foundation...

89
00:10:23,739 --> 00:10:26,367
my daughter, Mary Corleone.

90
00:10:36,118 --> 00:10:37,073
Thanks.

91
00:10:38,754 --> 00:10:42,679
l think l inherited my father's love
for speechmaking...

92
00:10:42,792 --> 00:10:44,225
but here it goes.

93
00:10:45,394 --> 00:10:47,282
The Vito Corleone Foundation...

94
00:10:47,396 --> 00:10:49,990
helps the impoverished
of every country...

95
00:10:50,099 --> 00:10:52,488
gives grants to artists...

96
00:10:52,602 --> 00:10:54,900
funds medical research...

97
00:10:55,004 --> 00:10:59,737
and is particularly dedicated
to the resurrection of Sicily.

98
00:10:59,842 --> 00:11:02,174
Archbishop Gilday...

99
00:11:02,278 --> 00:11:06,703
here is $ 1 00 million
for the poor of Sicily...

100
00:11:06,816 --> 00:11:09,011
in the name of Vito Corleone.

101
00:11:09,118 --> 00:11:11,916
Don't spend it all in one place.

102
00:11:33,509 --> 00:11:35,636
l'm so proud of you.

103
00:11:43,719 --> 00:11:47,143
You've done a wonderful thing
for Sicily.

104
00:11:47,256 --> 00:11:51,283
Let's just hope the money
gets to the people who need it.

105
00:11:51,394 --> 00:11:55,160
- Amen.
- But the most important part--

106
00:11:55,264 --> 00:11:57,186
Johnny Fontane!

107
00:12:06,142 --> 00:12:07,905
Thank you very much.

108
00:12:08,010 --> 00:12:10,899
l'm happy to be here with you,
and l'd like you to join me...

109
00:12:11,013 --> 00:12:14,642
in honoring
commendatore Michael Corleone.

110
00:12:19,088 --> 00:12:22,478
l have something special
for our host and godfather.

111
00:12:22,592 --> 00:12:25,117
l just happen to know
his favorite song.

112
00:12:25,227 --> 00:12:27,149
Michael, where are you going?
lt's your favorite song.

113
00:12:27,263 --> 00:12:30,687
l'm off here to the kitchen
to hear some Tony Bennett records.

114
00:12:32,435 --> 00:12:34,767
It's your favorite song.
It's salsiccia's own.

115
00:12:34,870 --> 00:12:36,701
We're getting
a salsiccia sandwich.

116
00:12:36,806 --> 00:12:38,239
l'll be back.

117
00:12:42,578 --> 00:12:45,467
A rose must remain

118
00:12:45,581 --> 00:12:48,141
With the sun and the rain

119
00:12:48,250 --> 00:12:53,040
Or its lovely promise
won't come true

120
00:12:54,223 --> 00:12:56,987
To each his own

121
00:12:57,093 --> 00:13:01,223
To each his own

122
00:13:01,330 --> 00:13:04,925
And my own is you

123
00:13:12,675 --> 00:13:14,700
Hello, Kay.

124
00:13:24,520 --> 00:13:27,614
Congratulations, Michael.
That's really quite an honor.

125
00:13:27,723 --> 00:13:30,647
lt's a little expensive,
wouldn't you say?

126
00:13:33,329 --> 00:13:35,251
Cake?

127
00:13:35,364 --> 00:13:37,025
No, thank you.

128
00:13:50,680 --> 00:13:53,569
- Been a long time, hasn't it?
- Yeah.

129
00:13:53,683 --> 00:13:56,072
Eight years.

130
00:13:56,185 --> 00:13:58,073
You look wonderful.

131
00:14:01,857 --> 00:14:04,223
Your son has something
he wants to talk to you about.

132
00:14:04,326 --> 00:14:06,658
l came here for him.

133
00:14:09,131 --> 00:14:11,019
Nice to see you.
Thank you.

134
00:14:15,438 --> 00:14:18,271
If a flame is to grow

135
00:14:18,374 --> 00:14:21,730
There must be a glow

136
00:14:21,844 --> 00:14:24,438
To open each door

137
00:14:24,547 --> 00:14:27,277
There's a key

138
00:14:27,383 --> 00:14:30,238
I need you, I know

139
00:14:30,352 --> 00:14:32,980
I can't let you go

140
00:14:40,930 --> 00:14:43,990
- What's wrong with being a lawyer?
- Nothing, except he doesn't want it.

141
00:14:44,100 --> 00:14:46,989
He wants his life
to be in music.

142
00:14:48,370 --> 00:14:50,759
Music is great.
l love music...

143
00:14:50,873 --> 00:14:53,262
but he should finish
what he started.

144
00:14:54,643 --> 00:14:57,976
- l'm going my own way.
- Your own way?

145
00:14:58,080 --> 00:14:59,707
- Professional singer?
- That's right.

146
00:14:59,815 --> 00:15:03,239
And what happens if you fail?

147
00:15:03,352 --> 00:15:05,274
l won't fail.

148
00:15:05,387 --> 00:15:07,719
- Men always believe that.
- l know.

149
00:15:07,823 --> 00:15:09,711
lf you have a law degree...

150
00:15:09,825 --> 00:15:11,713
you're taking out
insurance.

151
00:15:11,827 --> 00:15:13,852
After that, you can do anything--
work for me--

152
00:15:13,963 --> 00:15:16,158
l will never work for you.

153
00:15:16,265 --> 00:15:18,096
l have bad memories.

154
00:15:20,536 --> 00:15:23,164
Every family has bad memories.

155
00:15:26,976 --> 00:15:29,069
l will always be your son...

156
00:15:29,178 --> 00:15:33,740
but l will never have anything
to do with your business.

157
00:15:33,849 --> 00:15:37,706
Anthony, finish the law degree.

158
00:15:57,373 --> 00:16:01,696
That he got from you,
that ''no.''

159
00:16:04,513 --> 00:16:07,710
You could have helped me
to convince him, Kay.

160
00:16:07,817 --> 00:16:09,705
Oh, yeah.
Convince him of what?

161
00:16:09,819 --> 00:16:12,310
Of what?

162
00:16:12,388 --> 00:16:15,152
He throws his life away.

163
00:16:15,257 --> 00:16:17,213
He throws greatness away.

164
00:16:18,294 --> 00:16:21,252
This is greatness?

165
00:16:21,363 --> 00:16:23,251
Now that you're
so respectable...

166
00:16:23,365 --> 00:16:25,731
l think you're more dangerous
than you ever were.

167
00:16:25,835 --> 00:16:27,791
ln fact, l preferred you
when you were just...

168
00:16:27,903 --> 00:16:30,235
a common Mafia hood.

169
00:16:33,709 --> 00:16:37,065
- Now can we talk common sense here?
- All right.

170
00:16:43,886 --> 00:16:46,844
Tony knows that you killed Fredo.

171
00:16:53,128 --> 00:16:56,484
- What did you come here for?
- To protect my son.

172
00:16:56,599 --> 00:16:59,193
l didn't come to see you disguised
by your church.

173
00:16:59,301 --> 00:17:01,690
l think that was
a shameful ceremony.

174
00:17:05,975 --> 00:17:08,773
l spent my life
protecting my son.

175
00:17:08,878 --> 00:17:12,769
l spent my life
protecting my family!

176
00:17:12,882 --> 00:17:15,771
Let's be reasonable.

177
00:17:15,885 --> 00:17:19,673
That's your big thing,
isn't it, Michael?

178
00:17:19,788 --> 00:17:23,952
Reason backed up by murder.

179
00:17:24,059 --> 00:17:25,720
Oh, God.

180
00:17:26,996 --> 00:17:29,556
God, you hate me. You hate me.

181
00:17:30,332 --> 00:17:32,425
l don't hate you.

182
00:17:33,669 --> 00:17:35,068
l dread you.

183
00:17:39,475 --> 00:17:42,899
l did what l could, Kay, to protect...

184
00:17:43,012 --> 00:17:45,674
all of you from the horrors
of this world.

185
00:17:47,082 --> 00:17:48,970
But you became my horror.

186
00:17:58,761 --> 00:18:01,093
Our children still love you, though.

187
00:18:01,196 --> 00:18:02,891
Especially Mary.

188
00:18:05,601 --> 00:18:07,159
That's something.

189
00:18:09,705 --> 00:18:13,527
We can build on that,
for their sake.

190
00:18:17,313 --> 00:18:18,940
Let's try.

191
00:18:19,048 --> 00:18:22,279
Only if you let Tony go free
to have his own life...

192
00:18:23,385 --> 00:18:24,511
away from you.

193
00:18:31,760 --> 00:18:33,648
l'll let Tony go.

194
00:18:36,165 --> 00:18:37,792
Thank you.

195
00:19:16,372 --> 00:19:18,294
You could hurt somebody
with those.

196
00:19:19,708 --> 00:19:21,664
Let me show you around.

197
00:19:21,777 --> 00:19:24,143
Can you get me an interview
with Michael Corleone?

198
00:19:24,246 --> 00:19:27,101
No. l'm a relative,
but l can't do that.

199
00:19:27,216 --> 00:19:29,844
What else could l do for you?

200
00:19:29,952 --> 00:19:32,546
- Handsome but useless.
- Oh, yeah?

201
00:19:32,654 --> 00:19:35,851
- That's okay. l'll gamble.
- You like to gamble?

202
00:19:35,958 --> 00:19:39,985
Let's go to Atlantic City. lt's my town.
l'll show you how to gamble.

203
00:19:40,095 --> 00:19:42,461
How will l know
what numbers to bet?

204
00:19:42,564 --> 00:19:44,327
Do l look like a loser?

205
00:19:44,433 --> 00:19:45,923
Well--

206
00:19:48,337 --> 00:19:50,760
That's a spooky-looking
guy there.

207
00:19:50,873 --> 00:19:54,400
What's a guy like that doing
at Michael Corleone's house?

208
00:19:54,510 --> 00:19:56,842
- That's Joey Zasa's bulldog.
- You know that guy?

209
00:19:56,945 --> 00:19:59,072
Yeah, l know that guy.

210
00:19:59,181 --> 00:20:02,070
That guy's name
is Anthony Squigiliaro.

211
00:20:02,184 --> 00:20:04,106
They call him ''the Ant.''

212
00:20:04,219 --> 00:20:07,552
He dips his bullets in cyanide.

213
00:20:15,697 --> 00:20:17,460
Don Altobello.

214
00:20:19,101 --> 00:20:21,490
l come to pay my respects.

215
00:20:26,008 --> 00:20:28,431
You honor my father's friendship.

216
00:20:28,544 --> 00:20:30,705
Where is my goddaughter?

217
00:20:35,384 --> 00:20:39,650
lt was not so long ago
l held you in these old hands.

218
00:20:45,127 --> 00:20:47,755
No, no.
l stand. l stand.

219
00:20:47,863 --> 00:20:51,287
Michael, l lost
all the venom...

220
00:20:51,400 --> 00:20:53,288
all the juice of youth.

221
00:20:53,402 --> 00:20:55,427
l lost the lust
for women...

222
00:20:55,537 --> 00:20:59,029
and now my mind is clear.

223
00:20:59,141 --> 00:21:02,030
My duty to God is clear.

224
00:21:02,144 --> 00:21:05,534
l have a special favor to ask.

225
00:21:07,216 --> 00:21:11,448
Can l attach my name...

226
00:21:11,553 --> 00:21:14,442
to the Vito Corleone Foundation...

227
00:21:14,556 --> 00:21:17,286
so that you and l can be joined...

228
00:21:17,392 --> 00:21:20,088
in name and spirit?

229
00:21:22,431 --> 00:21:24,126
One million dollars.

230
00:21:30,272 --> 00:21:32,695
- Godfather.
- Don Altobello...

231
00:21:32,808 --> 00:21:34,696
you have such a heart.

232
00:21:37,212 --> 00:21:39,840
Come, let's go
and sample some of it.

233
00:21:48,056 --> 00:21:51,548
The Vatican knows nothing
about these shareholders.

234
00:21:51,660 --> 00:21:55,050
Good.
l have a tendency to worry.

235
00:21:55,164 --> 00:21:57,962
We've increased our position
substantially...

236
00:21:58,066 --> 00:21:59,226
and naturally, l worry.

237
00:21:59,334 --> 00:22:00,961
Come along now.
Stop worrying.

238
00:22:01,069 --> 00:22:03,458
We have an agreement.

239
00:22:03,572 --> 00:22:06,234
Good. How do you think
l got this gray hair?

240
00:22:06,341 --> 00:22:07,638
Mr. Corleone.

241
00:22:07,743 --> 00:22:09,802
- Two seconds.
- Frank, how are you?

242
00:22:09,912 --> 00:22:12,403
Thanks for your swimming pool
contribution...

243
00:22:12,514 --> 00:22:16,746
and we need your help on
Sam Wallace's candidacy for a judgeship.

244
00:22:16,852 --> 00:22:19,082
- We always can use a good judge.
- Thank you.

245
00:22:19,188 --> 00:22:21,053
Andrew.

246
00:22:21,156 --> 00:22:23,488
Excellency, my godson,
Andrew Hagen...

247
00:22:23,592 --> 00:22:25,480
my brother Tom Hagen's
eldest boy...

248
00:22:25,594 --> 00:22:28,984
and he's been assistant
to Bishop Breelan three years now.

249
00:22:29,097 --> 00:22:31,429
He's hoping for
a Vatican assignment.

250
00:22:31,533 --> 00:22:34,127
There's always a place in Rome
for a fine priest.

251
00:22:34,236 --> 00:22:36,659
His mother, Theresa Hagen.
Bishop Gilday.

252
00:22:36,772 --> 00:22:39,434
Thank you.
lt's an honor to meet you.

253
00:22:39,541 --> 00:22:44,001
Mr. Corleone, hi.
Grace Hamilton.

254
00:22:44,112 --> 00:22:46,603
Vincent Mancini promised
he'd tell you about me...

255
00:22:46,682 --> 00:22:48,946
that maybe you'd see me.

256
00:22:49,051 --> 00:22:50,814
Vincent Mancini call about her?

257
00:22:50,919 --> 00:22:52,318
No.

258
