01:23:37,696 --> 01:23:42,429
What do you know
about those pezzonovante in ltaly?

1008
01:23:46,338 --> 01:23:50,126
l'm too old to know anything
about those new people.

1009
01:23:50,242 --> 01:23:54,872
l must accept my age
and grow my olives and tomatoes.

1010
01:23:56,148 --> 01:24:00,903
- We're not that old.
- But you're very ill.

1011
01:24:03,688 --> 01:24:06,020
Let me see what can be done.

1012
01:24:06,124 --> 01:24:10,549
Let me work to make your path
a little easier.

1013
01:24:10,662 --> 01:24:13,927
Your friendship does that always.

1014
01:24:14,032 --> 01:24:15,920
That makes me happy.

1015
01:24:18,870 --> 01:24:20,303
You were wrong about him.

1016
01:24:21,640 --> 01:24:25,030
l trust too much.
That's always been my fault.

1017
01:24:34,820 --> 01:24:36,811
Treachery is everywhere.

1018
01:24:36,922 --> 01:24:42,610
You still have your fingers
on the strings, even now.

1019
01:24:42,727 --> 01:24:45,116
Let's see more of each other.

1020
01:24:47,499 --> 01:24:49,888
- In Sicily?
- In Sicily.

1021
01:25:43,192 --> 01:25:45,524
How are you?

1022
01:25:45,628 --> 01:25:48,153
Don Bendino, my old friend.

1023
01:26:19,495 --> 01:26:21,554
l wanted to bring you here...

1024
01:26:21,664 --> 01:26:25,293
so that my old friend and protector,
Don Tommasino...

1025
01:26:25,401 --> 01:26:27,289
could advise us.

1026
01:26:45,621 --> 01:26:49,580
The bloodbath in Atlantic City
left New York a mess.

1027
01:26:49,692 --> 01:26:53,150
Now,Joey Zasa at least was running
a fairly tight ship.

1028
01:26:53,262 --> 01:26:56,754
But now that he's out of the picture,
we're obligated to step in.

1029
01:26:56,866 --> 01:26:58,925
Step back in?

1030
01:26:59,035 --> 01:27:01,424
lf we don't,
the Chinese and Colombians will.

1031
01:27:32,735 --> 01:27:36,466
Our ships must all sail
in the same direction.

1032
01:27:37,773 --> 01:27:40,833
ltalian politics have had
these kind of men for centuries.

1033
01:27:40,943 --> 01:27:43,434
They are the true Mafia.

1034
01:27:43,546 --> 01:27:46,902
The archbishop and the Vatican Bank,
that's the big problem.

1035
01:27:47,016 --> 01:27:51,339
They're the same problem.
BJ, they're connected.

1036
01:27:51,454 --> 01:27:54,480
The archbishop has
very powerful friends.

1037
01:27:57,493 --> 01:27:59,324
They totally protect him.

1038
01:28:24,954 --> 01:28:27,548
l will go see
this Cardinal Lamberto...

1039
01:28:27,657 --> 01:28:30,512
and see if we can work things out
in a civilized way.

1040
01:28:32,428 --> 01:28:34,487
You honor your agreements...

1041
01:28:34,597 --> 01:28:37,122
but these people
you're dealing with are crooks.

1042
01:28:37,233 --> 01:28:39,121
They have no honor.

1043
01:28:42,238 --> 01:28:43,728
My word is final.

1044
01:29:21,110 --> 01:29:23,203
l've invited you all here...

1045
01:29:23,312 --> 01:29:27,544
to celebrate my son's
first appearance in an opera house.

1046
01:29:27,650 --> 01:29:29,208
- We're playing Philadelphia.
- He'll be appearing...

1047
01:29:29,318 --> 01:29:31,274
- What's Philadelphia?
- in about three weeks...

1048
01:29:31,387 --> 01:29:33,446
Seven cards, two down,
four up, one down...

1049
01:29:33,556 --> 01:29:35,512
- at the Theatre Massimo...
- deuces and one-eyed jacks are wild.

1050
01:29:35,625 --> 01:29:38,253
in the opera ''Cavallaria''Rusticana.

1051
01:29:38,361 --> 01:29:42,183
lt's Cavalleria Rusticana.

1052
01:29:42,298 --> 01:29:45,222
l think l got tickets
to the wrong opera.

1053
01:29:45,334 --> 01:29:48,497
l've been in New York too long.
Anyway...

1054
01:29:48,604 --> 01:29:52,165
you will all receive tickets,
so come on time.

1055
01:29:52,275 --> 01:29:54,163
Dad, l've got a present for you.

1056
01:29:58,347 --> 01:30:00,474
lt comes from the town of Corleone...

1057
01:30:00,583 --> 01:30:02,608
and it's authentic Sicilian.

1058
01:30:03,719 --> 01:30:07,280
And l learned it for you.

1059
01:31:36,545 --> 01:31:40,641
She was wonderful, beautiful,
and I loved her.

1060
01:31:40,750 --> 01:31:42,980
Then she died.

1061
01:31:43,085 --> 01:31:46,680
My trusted bodyguard...

1062
01:31:46,789 --> 01:31:50,020
planted a bomb in my car.

1063
01:31:50,126 --> 01:31:52,014
She drove it before l did.

1064
01:31:53,629 --> 01:31:57,292
Why is such a beautiful country
so violent?

1065
01:31:57,400 --> 01:31:58,958
History.

1066
01:31:59,068 --> 01:32:01,332
Mom was telling me about the old days.

1067
01:32:01,437 --> 01:32:05,567
- Your biggest worry was passing exams.
- Yes, it was then.

1068
01:32:05,674 --> 01:32:07,665
l worry about you now.

1069
01:32:09,345 --> 01:32:12,906
Mary, you're such a warmhearted girl.
You always were.

1070
01:32:13,015 --> 01:32:16,746
- l love my family.
- Even your cousin Vincent?

1071
01:32:20,756 --> 01:32:22,519
l really love him.

1072
01:32:23,993 --> 01:32:28,225
- He's your first cousin.
- Then l love him first.

1073
01:32:28,330 --> 01:32:31,060
Mary, you can't see him.

1074
01:32:31,167 --> 01:32:34,523
Just don't see him anymore.

1075
01:32:34,637 --> 01:32:38,459
He's right.
lt's too dangerous.

1076
01:32:41,043 --> 01:32:44,376
Listen to me.
You can't see him anymore.

1077
01:32:44,480 --> 01:32:46,209
- Not in that fashion.
- No.

1078
01:32:48,050 --> 01:32:50,143
Please, promise me.

1079
01:32:51,420 --> 01:32:53,718
- Obey me on this.
- No, Dad!

1080
01:32:59,161 --> 01:33:03,484
Mary's smart, Dad.
She'll understand eventually.

1081
01:33:40,469 --> 01:33:43,666
- You wanted to see me?
- Yeah.

1082
01:33:43,772 --> 01:33:46,434
- l want you to do something for me.
- Okay.

1083
01:33:46,542 --> 01:33:48,965
lt's dangerous.

1084
01:33:49,078 --> 01:33:53,003
Good, l'm in.
What do you need?

1085
01:33:53,115 --> 01:33:56,812
l want you to sell your soul
to Don Altobello...

1086
01:33:56,919 --> 01:33:58,807
to betray me.

1087
01:34:02,157 --> 01:34:04,921
He'd never believe me.
Here.

1088
01:34:05,027 --> 01:34:07,257
- That depends.
- Sit down.

1089
01:34:10,499 --> 01:34:12,387
l have an idea.

1090
01:34:13,669 --> 01:34:17,560
See if you can learn
how high Altobello is connected.

1091
01:34:21,343 --> 01:34:23,231
Arrange a meeting.

1092
01:34:25,781 --> 01:34:30,912
You say how devoted you are to me.
Tell him your problems.

1093
01:34:31,020 --> 01:34:33,909
- You ask for his help.
- What problems?

1094
01:34:36,091 --> 01:34:37,979
That you want to run away
with my daughter.

1095
01:34:39,628 --> 01:34:44,019
Only you know that if you do,
l will become your enemy.

1096
01:34:48,771 --> 01:34:51,001
You know l would never do that,
Uncle Mike.

1097
01:34:51,106 --> 01:34:52,164
l know.

1098
01:34:53,442 --> 01:34:56,366
You ask Altobello to speak to me...

1099
01:34:56,478 --> 01:34:58,434
to further the marriage.

1100
01:34:58,547 --> 01:35:00,845
But you're cousins, after all.

1101
01:35:00,950 --> 01:35:04,374
Michael was always
a little old-fashioned.

1102
01:35:04,486 --> 01:35:05,544
Explain to him how...

1103
01:35:05,654 --> 01:35:07,918
you could never be a part
of my legitimate world...

1104
01:35:08,023 --> 01:35:09,581
that you want your own family.

1105
01:35:09,692 --> 01:35:13,583
l could straighten out
what Zasa left behind.

1106
01:35:15,331 --> 01:35:17,720
l could use your friendship
to persuade him.

1107
01:35:19,268 --> 01:35:21,657
l would be indebted to you forever.

1108
01:35:24,139 --> 01:35:28,030
Corleones know the value
of such a friend.

1109
01:35:29,511 --> 01:35:31,900
So then you would work for me?

1110
01:35:40,556 --> 01:35:42,217
Remember...

1111
01:35:42,324 --> 01:35:47,250
if he hints that he wants you
to betray me, get insulted...

1112
01:35:47,363 --> 01:35:49,285
because that's his trap.

1113
01:35:56,939 --> 01:35:59,828
You're not telling me
the whole truth.

1114
01:36:03,412 --> 01:36:07,143
lsn't it true, with Michael gone...

1115
01:36:07,249 --> 01:36:09,638
the girl controls everything?

1116
01:36:13,155 --> 01:36:15,248
You leave the girl out of this.

1117
01:36:15,357 --> 01:36:18,747
Of course, you love her,
and she loves you.

1118
01:36:39,682 --> 01:36:42,071
l guessed it, huh?

1119
01:36:43,719 --> 01:36:47,109
You're a wise man, Don Altobello.

1120
01:36:47,222 --> 01:36:49,850
l'm gonna be learning a lot
from you.

1121
01:36:49,958 --> 01:36:52,688
The richest man is the one
with the most powerful friends.

1122
01:36:55,464 --> 01:36:58,627
lt's my duty to make
the introductions.

1123
01:37:05,607 --> 01:37:07,495
Don Lucchesi.

1124
01:37:10,345 --> 01:37:12,973
Don Altobello tells me
you have a good character...

1125
01:37:13,082 --> 01:37:16,142
strong,
a man of respect.

1126
01:37:16,251 --> 01:37:20,039
This is the hero
who put Joey Zasa in his grave.

1127
01:37:20,155 --> 01:37:24,444
lf we'd have known of his existence,
we would never have backed Joey.

1128
01:37:24,560 --> 01:37:26,448
No one wants another Joe.

1129
01:37:28,397 --> 01:37:29,694
Let me be your friend.

1130
01:37:31,433 --> 01:37:34,357
Even the strongest man needs friends.

1131
01:37:34,470 --> 01:37:36,859
l'm flattered.

1132
01:37:36,972 --> 01:37:39,566
You're a man of finance and politics,
Don Lucchesi.

1133
01:37:39,675 --> 01:37:41,563
These are things l don't understand.

1134
01:37:43,345 --> 01:37:44,573
You understand guns.

1135
01:37:45,514 --> 01:37:47,539
Finance is a gun.

1136
01:37:47,649 --> 01:37:52,245
Politics is knowing
when to pull the trigger.

1137
01:37:56,792 --> 01:37:58,020
How can l help?

1138
01:38:03,699 --> 01:38:06,293
Blessed is the peacemaker...

1139
01:38:06,401 --> 01:38:09,290
for he can be called
the child of God.

1140
01:38:45,507 --> 01:38:49,068
l trusted this business arrangement
with the archbishop.

1141
01:38:49,178 --> 01:38:54,275
l trusted him. l was sure
his honesty was beyond a doubt.

1142
01:38:54,383 --> 01:38:59,673
But, as you see,
l'm now the victim of a swindle.

1143
01:38:59,788 --> 01:39:01,676
He's stalling me.

1144
01:39:01,790 --> 01:39:05,749
Vast money have gone to the pezzonovante
in high political places...

1145
01:39:05,861 --> 01:39:08,591
and the Vatican Bank
is the guarantor.

1146
01:39:08,697 --> 01:39:13,953
lf what you say is true,
there will be a great scandal.

1147
01:39:15,938 --> 01:39:21,069
Look at this stone. lt has been lying
in the water for a very long time...

1148
01:39:21,176 --> 01:39:25,067
but the water has not penetrated it.

1149
01:39:29,117 --> 01:39:33,008
Look, perfectly dry.

1150
01:39:34,256 --> 01:39:36,622
The same thing has happened
to men in Europe.

1151
01:39:36,725 --> 01:39:41,617
For centuries, they have been
surrounded by Christianity...

1152
01:39:41,730 --> 01:39:44,255
but Christ has not penetrated.

1153
01:39:44,366 --> 01:39:47,756
Christ doesn't live within them.

1154
01:39:51,807 --> 01:39:53,934
- What's happening?
- ls it possible...

1155
01:39:54,042 --> 01:39:56,966
that you could get me something sweet.

1156
01:39:57,079 --> 01:39:59,468
Orange juice, anything, a candy.

1157
01:40:03,051 --> 01:40:05,110
l have a little trouble with diabetes.

1158
01:40:09,091 --> 01:40:10,979
Blood sugar goes low.

1159
01:40:12,127 --> 01:40:14,015
l understand.

1160
01:40:36,518 --> 01:40:40,181
When l'm under stress,
sometimes this happens.

1161
01:40:40,289 --> 01:40:42,177
l understand.

1162
01:40:44,026 --> 01:40:47,416
To come to you
on such a delicate matter...

1163
01:40:50,565 --> 01:40:53,523
accusations against your archbishop.

1164
01:40:53,635 --> 01:40:55,694
lt was difficult for me.

1165
01:40:56,939 --> 01:40:59,134
The mind suffers...

1166
01:40:59,241 --> 01:41:02,870
and the body cries out.

1167
01:41:07,716 --> 01:41:09,775
That's true.

1168
01:41:11,253 --> 01:41:15,576
Would you like to make
your confession?

1169
01:41:22,230 --> 01:41:24,289
Your Eminence, l'm--

1170
01:41:28,103 --> 01:41:29,832
lt's been so long.

1171
01:41:29,938 --> 01:41:33,328
l wouldn't know where to--

1172
01:41:35,077 --> 01:41:36,965
lt's been 30 years.

1173
01:41:39,114 --> 01:41:41,605
l'd use up too much of your time,
l think.

1174
01:41:41,717 --> 01:41:44,811
l always have time to save souls.

1175
01:41:46,221 --> 01:41:49,110
Well, l'm beyond redemption.

1176
01:42:00,435 --> 01:42:05,395
l hear the confessions
of my own priests here.

1177
01:42:05,507 --> 01:42:09,329
Sometimes the desire to confess
is overwhelming...

1178
01:42:09,444 --> 01:42:11,833
and we must seize the moment.

1179
01:42:16,852 --> 01:42:21,380
What is the point of confessing
if l don't repent?

1180
01:42:23,091 --> 01:42:26,390
l hear you are a practical man.

1181
01:42:26,495 --> 01:42:29,555
What have you got to lose, huh?

1182
01:42:40,475 --> 01:42:42,705
Go on.

1183
01:42:48,650 --> 01:42:50,049
l...

1184
01:42:51,186 --> 01:42:53,074
betrayed my wife.

1185
01:42:54,723 --> 01:42:56,611
Go on, my son.

1186
01:43:02,030 --> 01:43:03,918
l betrayed myself.

1187
01:43:06,802 --> 01:43:08,690
l killed men.

1188
01:43:12,441 --> 01:43:14,830
And l ordered men to be killed.

1189
01:43:16,478 --> 01:43:18,366
Go on, my son, go on.

1190
01:43:24,519 --> 01:43:25,747
lt's useless.

1191
01:43:27,823 --> 01:43:29,711
Go on, my son.

1192
01:43:30,826 --> 01:43:32,714
l killed--

1193
01:43:37,466 --> 01:43:41,129
l ordered the death of my brother.

1194
01:43:41,236 --> 01:43:43,124
He injured me.

1195
01:43:44,539 --> 01:43:47,133
l killed my mother's son.

1196
01:43:48,510 --> 01:43:50,603
l killed my father's son.

1197
01:44:01,323 --> 01:44:03,348
Your sins are terrible...

1198
01:44:03,458 --> 01:44:06,018
and it is just
that you suffer.

1199
01:44:07,295 --> 01:44:09,684
Your life could be redeemed...

1200
01:44:10,932 --> 01:44:12,820
but l know
that you don't believe that.

1201
01:44:12,934 --> 01:44:14,822
You will not change.

1202
01:45:10,425 --> 01:45:14,316
All my life
l kept trying to go up in society...

1203
01:45:15,564 --> 01:45:18,954
where everything higher up
was legal, straight.

1204
01:45:20,435 --> 01:45:23,495
But the higher l go,
the more crooked it becomes.

1205
01:45:26,775 --> 01:45:28,834
Where the hell does it end?

1206
01:45:37,919 --> 01:45:40,808
Killing each other
for centuries here.

1207
01:45:42,657 --> 01:45:47,014
For money, for pride, for family.

1208
01:45:50,098 --> 01:45:53,989
To keep from becoming the slaves
of the rich pezzonovante.

1209
01:46:01,142 --> 01:46:03,201
l made confession, Connie.

1210
01:46:04,312 --> 01:46:06,940
l confessed my sins.

1211
01:46:08,049 --> 01:46:10,540
Why, Michael?
That's not like you.

1212
01:46:10,652 --> 01:46:14,008
You don't have to confess your sins
to a stranger.

1213
01:46:14,122 --> 01:46:15,555
lt was the man.

1214
01:46:16,958 --> 01:46:19,085
A good man...

1215
01:46:19,194 --> 01:46:21,082
a true priest.

1216
01:46:24,799 --> 01:46:26,687
He can change things.

1217
01:46:32,073 --> 01:46:33,802
You know...

1218
01:46:33,908 --> 01:46:37,298
sometimes l think of poor Fredo--
drowned.

1219
01:46:38,880 --> 01:46:40,768
lt was God's will.

1220
01:46:42,651 --> 01:46:45,040
lt was a terrible accident.

1221
01:46:46,154 --> 01:46:48,042
But it's finished.

1222
01:46:53,461 --> 01:46:55,349
Michael, l love you.

1223
01:46:57,732 --> 01:46:59,620
l'll always help you.

1224
01:47:09,444 --> 01:47:11,332
lt's okay.

1225
01:49:51,473 --> 01:49:53,964
- Welcome.
- How are you?

1226
01:49:54,075 --> 01:49:57,567
- Mary, l missed you.
- l missed you too.

1227
01:49:57,679 --> 01:49:59,567
- Hello, Michael.
- Hello.

1228
01:49:59,681 --> 01:50:01,740
- Mom, look at this.
- What?

1229
01:50:03,418 --> 01:50:05,147
Oh, my--

1230
01:50:05,253 --> 01:50:07,380
You know, it's too bad
that Douglas couldn't be with us.

1231
01:50:07,489 --> 01:50:11,186
No, l know. He wanted to come very much,
but he had a very important trial.

1232
01:50:11,292 --> 01:50:14,420
- l know he wanted to come.
- l know.

1233
01:50:14,529 --> 01:50:16,417
- The car is--
- Okay.

1234
01:50:18,466 --> 01:50:22,527
Well, your son's an artist, huh?

1235
01:50:22,637 --> 01:50:24,730
Oh, yes, thanks to you.

1236
01:50:24,839 --> 01:50:26,238
Oh, what for?

1237
01:50:27,408 --> 01:50:29,672
For making me let him go.

1238
01:50:29,777 --> 01:50:31,665
Oh, well.

1239
01:50:31,779 --> 01:50:35,510
After all these years, here l am
in Sicily for the first time.

1240
01:50:35,617 --> 01:50:38,006
- l want a picture of you together.
- Okay.

1241
01:50:40,688 --> 01:50:42,576
Hey, Dad, smile.

1242
01:50:46,561 --> 01:50:49,792
l see you still have Al Neri.
Why?

1243
01:50:51,232 --> 01:50:55,464
Well, l need him. He helps me
get in and out of the car.

1244
01:50:55,570 --> 01:50:57,868
He carries my briefcase.

1245
01:50:57,972 --> 01:51:00,668
You're still a liar, Michael.

1246
01:51:00,775 --> 01:51:04,233
Let me show you Sicily--
the real Sicily.

1247
01:51:04,345 --> 01:51:07,143
Maybe you'll understand
the family history a little better.

1248
01:51:07,248 --> 01:51:09,637
l think l understand it well enough.

1249
01:52:01,669 --> 01:52:05,059
Anthony, l have something
you made for me...

1250
01:52:06,274 --> 01:52:08,162
a very long time ago.

1251
01:52:09,344 --> 01:52:12,472
- To bring you luck.
- Thanks.

1252
01:52:16,217 --> 01:52:17,775
You saved it, huh?

1253
01:52:17,885 --> 01:52:20,376
- Remember?
- l remember.

1254
01:52:22,924 --> 01:52:24,812
Thank you.

1255
01:52:27,095 --> 01:52:28,494
Proud of you.

1256
01:52:29,430 --> 01:52:30,988
Thank you.

1257
01:52:47,181 --> 01:52:49,809
- Are they as good as they look?
- They're better.

1258
01:52:49,917 --> 01:52:52,442
They're the best.

1259
01:52:52,553 --> 01:52:54,748
As long as they're around,
Uncle Michael is safe.

1260
01:52:54,889 --> 01:52:56,254
Good-bye.

1261
01:52:59,360 --> 01:53:01,316
Tell your father
l'll be back for dinner.

1262
01:53:03,097 --> 01:53:05,759
- Have fun.
- Tell Tony to be sure and wait for me.

1263
01:53:05,867 --> 01:53:08,495
Okay, l will.

1264
01:53:08,603 --> 01:53:10,901
Bye, Mom!

1265
01:53:11,005 --> 01:53:13,235
At your service.

1266
01:53:16,844 --> 01:53:20,234
lf l see Dad,
l'll tell him you left.

1267
01:53:25,453 --> 01:53:29,378
You're the only one left in this family
with my father's strength.

1268
01:53:31,626 --> 01:53:36,222
lf anything happens to Michael,
l want you to strike back.

1269
01:53:38,700 --> 01:53:40,258
l'll have everything ready.

1270
01:53:44,038 --> 01:53:45,926
You swear?

1271
01:53:53,047 --> 01:53:55,106
l swear to you.

1272
01:54:25,313 --> 01:54:27,201
Here it is.

1273
01:54:28,616 --> 01:54:30,675
The house where my father was born.

1274
01:54:32,320 --> 01:54:36,711
This is where they came to take him
when he was a boy...

1275
01:54:36,824 --> 01:54:38,712
to kill him.

1276
01:54:41,028 --> 01:54:44,418
Wait, listen to that.

1277
01:55:04,685 --> 01:55:08,143
You know, Mary's in love.

1278
01:55:08,256 --> 01:55:10,781
Yes, l know.

1279
01:55:10,892 --> 01:55:16,023
With a handsome young ltalian man
with dark eyes.

1280
01:55:16,130 --> 01:55:18,018
l won't allow it.

1281
01:55:20,835 --> 01:55:24,532
lt's wrong.
lt's wrong, and it's dangerous.

1282
01:55:56,871 --> 01:55:58,532
Honor, huh?

1283
01:56:17,992 --> 01:56:20,950
You know, l remember the time
you came to my parents' house...

1284
01:56:21,062 --> 01:56:24,361
and you took me into that room
and told me about the family business...

1285
01:56:24,465 --> 01:56:28,162
and how you were never going to have
anything to do with it.

1286
01:56:28,269 --> 01:56:30,601
You sounded like Tony.

1287
01:56:30,705 --> 01:56:32,593
l was a lot like Tony.

1288
01:56:40,214 --> 01:56:43,172
- l can barely see. Kay.
- What?

1289
01:56:43,284 --> 01:56:45,946
- You mind driving?
- No. What's wrong?

1290
01:56:46,053 --> 01:56:49,682
My eyes-- sometimes
they're all right, and then--

1291
01:56:49,790 --> 01:56:52,918
- Sure.
- Listen, l have to see Don Tommasino.

1292
01:56:54,996 --> 01:56:56,759
Oh, my God!

1293
01:56:56,864 --> 01:56:58,263
Well--

1294
01:56:59,433 --> 01:57:02,823
- There's no bodyguards today.
- l really snuck away.

1295
01:57:56,023 --> 01:57:57,786
- How are you?
- Hi.

1296
01:57:57,892 --> 01:57:59,780
- Kay, this is Calo, my old friend.
- How do you do?

1297
01:57:59,894 --> 01:58:01,782
One of my bodyguards
in the old days.

1298
01:58:07,201 --> 01:58:08,600
- We can wait here.
- You want drink?

1299
01:58:08,703 --> 01:58:12,093
- Yes. Shall we go in?
- Sure.

1300
01:58:14,675 --> 01:58:17,064
l spent a lot of time in this room...

1301
01:58:19,413 --> 01:58:21,142
thinking of you.

1302
01:58:24,285 --> 01:58:26,845
And then you got married.

1303
01:58:30,024 --> 01:58:31,582
l still thought of you.

1304
01:58:32,360 --> 01:58:34,248
What's in that room?

1305
01:58:38,065 --> 01:58:42,354
l know this is dangerous for you.
This is Sicily.

1306
01:58:44,705 --> 01:58:47,094
- l love this country.
- Why?

1307
01:58:49,810 --> 01:58:53,166
Well, all through history...

1308
01:58:53,280 --> 01:58:55,612
terrible things
have happened to these people.

1309
01:58:55,716 --> 01:58:58,514
Terrible injustices.

1310
01:58:59,620 --> 01:59:04,853
But they still expect good
rather than bad will happen to them.

1311
01:59:04,959 --> 01:59:07,348
Sort of like me and you, huh?

1312
01:59:11,432 --> 01:59:14,788
- How so?
- l'm still here, right?

1313
01:59:14,902 --> 01:59:16,392
We do have a bad history.

1314
01:59:17,338 --> 01:59:20,762
- l'm still here.
- Yes, you are, but with dread.

1315
01:59:25,679 --> 01:59:27,442
Give me the order. Come on.

1316
01:59:27,548 --> 01:59:30,278
What is that supposed to do? ls that
supposed to make me not dread you?

1317
01:59:33,554 --> 01:59:35,943
We're in Sicily. lt's opera.

1318
01:59:38,359 --> 01:59:39,758
Okay.

1319
01:59:42,196 --> 01:59:44,255
What do we do now?

1320
01:59:47,068 --> 01:59:49,127
Be reasonable.

1321
01:59:49,236 --> 01:59:51,124
Let's try not to hurt each other.

1322
01:59:58,512 --> 02:00:00,400
l want you to forgive me.

1323
02:00:03,184 --> 02:00:04,242
For what?

1324
02:00:05,352 --> 02:00:06,910
Everything.

1325
02:00:11,192 --> 02:00:12,921
Like God, huh?

1326
02:00:14,161 --> 02:00:16,686
l need something a little closer.

1327
02:00:19,500 --> 02:00:22,355
You couldn't understand
back in those days...

1328
02:00:24,238 --> 02:00:26,160
l loved my father.

1329
02:00:26,273 --> 02:00:29,162
l swore l would never be
a man like him...

1330
02:00:29,276 --> 02:00:31,767
but l loved him,
and he was in danger.

1331
02:00:31,879 --> 02:00:33,767
What could l do?

1332
02:00:33,881 --> 02:00:37,146
And then later
you were in danger.

1333
02:00:37,251 --> 02:00:41,676
Our children were in danger.
What could l do?

1334
02:00:41,789 --> 02:00:45,281
You were all that l... loved...

1335
02:00:45,392 --> 02:00:47,781
valued most in the world.

1336
02:00:48,896 --> 02:00:51,456
And now l'm losing you.
l lost you anyway.

1337
02:00:52,666 --> 02:00:54,554
You're gone...

1338
02:00:55,669 --> 02:00:57,899
and it was all for nothing.

1339
02:00:58,005 --> 02:00:59,404
So--

1340
02:01:03,244 --> 02:01:05,804
You have to understand...

1341
02:01:05,913 --> 02:01:08,404
l had a whole different
destiny planned.

1342
02:01:11,986 --> 02:01:14,181
All right, l'll stop.

1343
02:01:24,398 --> 02:01:28,095
l really don't know what you want
from me, Michael. l really don't know.

1344
02:01:28,202 --> 02:01:33,333
- l mean--
- l'm not the man that you think l am?

1345
02:01:34,875 --> 02:01:38,732
- l don't know.
- l love you, Kay.

1346
02:01:39,947 --> 02:01:42,905
Don't dread me anymore.

1347
02:01:47,855 --> 02:01:50,085
You know...

1348
02:01:50,191 --> 02:01:52,580
every night here in Sicily...

1349
02:01:53,827 --> 02:01:55,522
l dream...

1350
02:01:56,864 --> 02:01:59,253
about my wife
and my children...

1351
02:02:02,503 --> 02:02:04,926
and how l lost them.

1352
02:02:06,607 --> 02:02:10,202
l guess, if it's any consolation...

1353
02:02:10,311 --> 02:02:12,302
l want you to know that...

1354
02:02:15,683 --> 02:02:17,082
that...

1355
02:02:18,352 --> 02:02:20,741
l always loved you, Michael.

1356
02:02:22,089 --> 02:02:25,422
And, you know...

1357
02:02:25,526 --> 02:02:27,915
l always will.

1358
02:03:26,320 --> 02:03:28,049
lt never ends.

1359
02:05:00,347 --> 02:05:02,269
Frederick Keinszig...

1360
02:05:02,383 --> 02:05:04,715
known for a decade as ''God's banker''...

1361
02:05:04,818 --> 02:05:06,740
has been reported missing.

1362
02:05:06,854 --> 02:05:08,742
He was last seen three days ago...

1363
02:05:08,856 --> 02:05:10,255
leaving the Rome offices...

1364
02:05:10,357 --> 02:05:14,123
of a Vatican-owned corporation,
International Immobiliare.

1365
02:05:14,228 --> 02:05:16,253
Also missing was a large sum of money...

1366
02:05:16,363 --> 02:05:18,388
and several documents.

1367
02:05:18,499 --> 02:05:20,888
Come on, Keinszig, you fool.

1368
02:05:24,905 --> 02:05:27,294
Mr. Keinszig's absence casts
further suspicion...

1369
02:05:27,408 --> 02:05:29,831
on the dealings
of the Vatican Bank.

1370
02:05:29,943 --> 02:05:32,776
For several years, the bank
and its subsidiary companies...

1371
02:05:32,880 --> 02:05:37,340
have been the object of allegations
of disreputable business practices.

1372
02:05:39,653 --> 02:05:42,542
Will you please try and understand?

1373
02:05:43,657 --> 02:05:45,579
l have phoned him.

1374
02:05:45,692 --> 02:05:48,081
l have waited here by the phone.

1375
02:05:50,597 --> 02:05:55,330
You would do well to remember,
Mr. Lucchesi...

1376
02:05:55,436 --> 02:06:00,430
that this pope
has very different ideas...

1377
02:06:00,541 --> 02:06:02,497
from the last one.

1378
02:06:24,064 --> 02:06:26,453
Good-bye, my old friend.

1379
02:06:28,168 --> 02:06:30,557
You could've lived
a little longer.

1380
02:06:32,272 --> 02:06:35,161
l could be closer to my dream.

1381
02:06:41,081 --> 02:06:43,641
You were so loved, Don Tommasino.

1382
02:06:48,655 --> 02:06:52,546
Why was l so feared,
and you were so loved?

1383
02:06:53,660 --> 02:06:56,151
What was it?

1384
02:06:56,230 --> 02:06:58,118
l was no less honorable.

1385
02:07:00,266 --> 02:07:02,154
l wanted to do good.

1386
02:07:06,472 --> 02:07:09,361
What betrayed me?
My mind? My heart?

1387
02:07:12,411 --> 02:07:14,800
Why do l condemn myself so?

1388
02:07:21,320 --> 02:07:25,711
l swear on the lives of my children...

1389
02:07:30,329 --> 02:07:33,218
give me a chance
to redeem myself...

1390
02:07:37,103 --> 02:07:40,994
and l will sin no more.

1391
02:08:04,163 --> 02:08:09,055
You look pale.
Bad news? Tell me right away.

1392
02:08:10,736 --> 02:08:14,263
lt's not just a bad banking deal.

1393
02:08:14,373 --> 02:08:16,261
These guys are butchers.

1394
02:08:17,576 --> 02:08:19,464
What guys?

1395
02:08:19,578 --> 02:08:23,571
Lucchesi--
he controls all of them.

1396
02:08:23,683 --> 02:08:26,572
Altobello, the archbishop...

1397
02:08:27,687 --> 02:08:30,451
other people higher up,
P2, maybe.

1398
02:08:30,556 --> 02:08:34,413
Secret, unknown.
They're running things.

1399
02:08:37,330 --> 02:08:40,219
- l'm in their way.
- Yeah.

1400
02:08:40,333 --> 02:08:42,756
He's hired a professional assassin
to kill you.

1401
02:08:42,868 --> 02:08:44,426
He's Sicilian.

1402
02:08:44,537 --> 02:08:48,928
l don't know his name,
but they say he never fails.

1403
02:08:51,077 --> 02:08:52,965
Then no one is safe.

1404
02:08:56,015 --> 02:08:58,404
Even the new pope
is in danger.

1405
02:08:59,585 --> 02:09:03,476
We still have time.
We can prevent this.

1406
02:09:08,027 --> 02:09:09,915
l tried.

1407
02:09:12,498 --> 02:09:17,390
l tried to keep everything
from coming to this.

1408
02:09:18,571 --> 02:09:23,565
But it's not possible,
not in this world.

1409
02:09:24,677 --> 02:09:26,599
Give me the order.

1410
02:09:30,149 --> 02:09:32,037
You won't be able to go back.

1411
02:09:33,352 --> 02:09:36,480
- You'll be like me.
- Good.

1412
02:09:36,589 --> 02:09:40,013
All my life l wanted out.

1413
02:09:40,126 --> 02:09:42,014
l wanted the family out.

1414
02:09:43,863 --> 02:09:46,024
Well, l don't want out.

1415
02:09:46,132 --> 02:09:49,522
l want the power
to preserve the family.

1416
02:09:54,173 --> 02:09:56,061
l'm asking for the order.

1417
02:10:17,129 --> 02:10:19,017
lt's done.

1418
02:10:20,466 --> 02:10:22,388
Because l can't do it anymore.

1419
02:10:26,605 --> 02:10:28,937
Well, it doesn't matter.

1420
02:10:29,041 --> 02:10:32,306
Vincent knows what to do.
Come on outside.

1421
02:10:32,411 --> 02:10:35,835
Take a rest
and don't think about it.

1422
02:10:35,948 --> 02:10:38,837
- All l do is think about it.
- l'm your son.

1423
02:10:40,119 --> 02:10:42,007
Command me in all things.

1424
02:10:44,623 --> 02:10:46,511
Give up my daughter.

1425
02:10:49,595 --> 02:10:51,483
That's the price you pay...

1426
02:10:52,765 --> 02:10:55,495
for the life you choose.

1427
02:11:21,227 --> 02:11:23,115
Nephew...

1428
02:11:25,097 --> 02:11:26,985
from this moment on...

1429
02:11:28,934 --> 02:11:30,822
call yourself Vincent Corleone.

1430
02:11:35,941 --> 02:11:37,340
Sit.

1431
02:13:43,435 --> 02:13:46,563
l know how you feel about Michael...

1432
02:13:46,672 --> 02:13:48,503
but you can't save him.

1433
02:13:48,607 --> 02:13:50,495
He's lost.

1434
02:13:52,211 --> 02:13:53,701
Think of yourself.

1435
02:13:55,014 --> 02:13:57,403
What's your answer?

1436
02:13:59,618 --> 02:14:01,506
Enjoy the opera.

1437
02:14:03,555 --> 02:14:05,443
lt's all taken care of.

1438
02:14:10,295 --> 02:14:12,684
Check the bar.
l'll check the top floor.

1439
02:14:17,002 --> 02:14:19,891
''Here's hoping Tony sings better
at the Theatro Massimo...

1440
02:14:20,005 --> 02:14:22,394
than he does in the shower--
Love, Douglas.''

1441
02:14:24,176 --> 02:14:26,064
My darling, Costanza.

1442
02:14:28,814 --> 02:14:31,203
- This is a great occasion.
- Come, sit down.

1443
02:14:36,321 --> 02:14:38,209
Happy birthday.

1444
02:14:38,323 --> 02:14:40,848
You're 80 years old,
you don't look more than 60.

1445
02:14:40,959 --> 02:14:42,586
You're the only one
who remembered.

1446
02:14:42,695 --> 02:14:45,061
Michael, we just got the word.

1447
02:14:45,164 --> 02:14:48,361
The pope's ratifying
the lmmobiliare deal. We've won.

1448
02:14:48,467 --> 02:14:50,355
Congratulations.

1449
02:14:53,138 --> 02:14:55,527
How strange, the way things work.

1450
02:14:55,641 --> 02:14:59,031
The pope's doing exactly what you said
he'd do. He's cleaning house.

1451
02:15:00,546 --> 02:15:05,108
He should be careful.
lt's dangerous to be an honest man.

1452
02:15:10,589 --> 02:15:12,978
l wanna put more muscle backstage
with Tony.

1453
02:15:25,704 --> 02:15:29,094
On your birthday,
you used to shower me with treats.

1454
02:15:29,208 --> 02:15:31,096
Tootsie Rolls.

1455
02:15:32,211 --> 02:15:35,169
The nuns who made these cannolis
took a vow of silence.

1456
02:15:35,280 --> 02:15:37,840
They're the very finest.

1457
02:15:43,255 --> 02:15:44,654
Hey, cous.

1458
02:15:47,659 --> 02:15:49,092
Where's your leather?

1459
02:15:52,831 --> 02:15:54,264
Stop it.

1460
02:16:00,439 --> 02:16:03,328
You're so thin.
You eat it.

1461
02:16:27,232 --> 02:16:31,623
lt's over. There are things l have to do
that you can't be a part of.

1462
02:16:31,737 --> 02:16:34,831
Don't look at your father. lt's not
your father's decision. lt's mine.

1463
02:16:36,575 --> 02:16:38,964
Don't hate your father.

1464
02:16:40,746 --> 02:16:44,568
There are things l wanna be a part of,
you can't be around.

1465
02:16:46,618 --> 02:16:49,007
After tonight,
you won't see me anymore.

1466
02:16:53,826 --> 02:16:56,522
You gotta understand.
You gotta understand.

1467
02:16:58,397 --> 02:17:00,285
l'll always love you.

1468
02:17:13,212 --> 02:17:14,702
Love somebody else.

1469
02:17:37,469 --> 02:17:39,357
- To Tony.
- To Tony.

1470
02:20:56,201 --> 02:21:00,262
- They won't try.anything.
- Yeah, everything is fine. lt's clear.

1471
02:21:00,372 --> 02:21:03,432
l've already sent Al Neri
to the Vatican.

1472
02:23:52,844 --> 02:23:55,074
Check out the side.

1473
02:26:18,623 --> 02:26:21,512
Good. You got him.

1474
02:27:13,378 --> 02:27:15,767
Tonight the Corleone family
settles its accounts.

1475
02:27:16,881 --> 02:27:18,803
Keinszig...

1476
02:27:18,917 --> 02:27:22,375
that little Swiss banker fuck.

1477
02:27:22,487 --> 02:27:27,151
He's been swindling everyone
from the beginning. Fuck him.

1478
02:27:28,092 --> 02:27:29,980
Don Lucchesi, my friend...

1479
02:27:30,929 --> 02:27:33,853
Calo will pay him a visit
at his home.

1480
02:27:36,134 --> 02:27:39,023
Neri, take a train to Rome.

1481
02:27:41,105 --> 02:27:42,993
Light a candle
for the archbishop.

1482
02:29:46,397 --> 02:29:49,855
Michael, it's serious.
Our man inside the Vatican says...

1483
02:29:49,968 --> 02:29:51,367
there's a plot
against the pope.

1484
02:29:51,469 --> 02:29:53,630
You mean, he's gonna have
a heart attack?

1485
02:30:00,912 --> 02:30:05,804
This pope has powerful enemies.
We may not be in time to save him.

1486
02:30:09,053 --> 02:30:10,452
Let's go back to the opera.

1487
02:32:35,366 --> 02:32:36,424
Sleep.

1488
02:32:37,635 --> 02:32:39,523
Sleep, Godfather.

1489
02:36:28,866 --> 02:36:31,061
- l like this outfit.
- Yeah, l figured you would.

1490
02:36:31,168 --> 02:36:33,659
- Bravo. Say hello.
- Thank you.

1491
02:36:39,844 --> 02:36:42,074
- Did you like it?
- Great.

1492
02:36:43,914 --> 02:36:46,246
Let's get out of here.

1493
02:36:55,826 --> 02:36:59,592
- Can l please talk to you now?
- Not now, it's not a good time.

1494
02:36:59,697 --> 02:37:03,588
- You're just like my father.
- Come on, stay with the family. Go on.

1495
02:37:05,136 --> 02:37:06,899
- Talk to me.
- The twins are dead.

1496
02:37:07,004 --> 02:37:10,895
ln about one minute, there's gonna be
carabinieri crawling all over the place.

1497
02:37:12,209 --> 02:37:14,769
Okay. Let's get everybody
to the cars, nice and quiet.

1498
02:37:14,879 --> 02:37:16,767
- Got it.
- Quiet.

1499
02:37:31,395 --> 02:37:34,489
When they hear the name Corleone,
they're gonna think of a voice.

1500
02:37:44,442 --> 02:37:46,137
Dad.

1501
02:37:54,118 --> 02:37:55,608
This is my mom.

1502
02:38:04,962 --> 02:38:08,989
Dad, why are you doing this to me?

1503
02:38:18,042 --> 02:38:21,466
- Go on, move back. Go on, move back.
- Hey, move!

1504
02:38:21,579 --> 02:38:24,776
- You don't have to do this to me.
